comments.body:
This is a little hard to read. A vanilla `if` statement may be better:

```
if (connectorName != null) {
    assertTrue(context.startsWith("[" + connectorName));
}
```

But that's not equivalent. It'd need to be:
```
if (connectorName != null) {
    assertTrue(context.startsWith("[" + connectorName));
} else {
    assertFalse(context.startsWith("[" + connectorName));
}
```
IMO, that's too verbose.

